<i>noun</i>: 방사선 [방ː사선], 발광 [발광] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>방사선 [방ː사선]</dt><br>
<dd>radiation</dd><br>
<dd>라듐, 우라늄 등의 방사성 원소가 작은 입자로 부서지면서 내쏘는 알파선, 감마선, 베타선 등의 전자파.</dd><br>
<dd>Electromagnetic waves such as the alpha ray, gamma ray, beta ray, etc., that are emitted as radioactive elements like radium, uranium, etc., are disassembled into small particles.</dd><br>
<dt>발광 [발광]</dt><br>
<dd>luminescence; radiation</dd><br>
<dd>빛을 냄.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of emitting light.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>